    <h4 class="title is-4 ">A couple of great ideas for your next side hustle.</h4>
    <article>
        <p>
            Most everyone wants to know the future. Since before prehistory, man has been looking to patterns: in the stars, in the shape and length of lines on their neighbor’s palm, or in the arrangement of the innards of the neighbor’s livestock’s
            ( or in some cases those of the neighbors). Today, all of that is unnecessary for all of us whether we live in Inglewood, Wedgewood, Woodbine, or yeah, Bellevue. And the reason is that the future is…Nashville.
        </p>

        <p>
            And why shouldn’t it be? One hundred some people step over each other to move here every day. There are cranes all over the city; more than anywhere else other than New York and Los Angeles. The British Museum had to recall an exhibit recently.
            Apparently, the exhibit was sensitive to vibrations, and this jackhammer happy city was simply too busy growing to accommodate the exhibit’s need for tranquility.
        </p>

        <p>
            People are moving here, businesses are moving here-opportunity is everywhere. Of course, those who are young, bright, armed with degrees and experience gleaned from mom and daddy financed unpaid internships will land somewhere in this fair
            city. But there are just as many who will have to make it by tending bar, waiting tables, working construction, etc. And no matter how restaurants you get hired and fired you’ll never make enough for rent. That is unless you plan on living
            with a half a dozen roommates or you intend on commuting from Alabama. And if you’re a publicist’s assistant and you want to live in the Gulch without a gazillion roommates? Hah!
        </p>

        <p>
            So how is a regular Joe or Jane supposed to make it in the big, expensive city of Nashville without money, degree, big break, connections, or whatever? The answer is by getting a side hustle. With a side hustle, you own your own business-it
            ’s all up to you how much money you make. Now what kind of side hustle would work and be unique and appropriate for The Music City? Let’s find out.
        </p>

        <p>Before we begin, let’s be clear. I did say ‘hustle’ which means you may stretch the truth and reality here and there. Don’t worry, our commander in chief does it so you can too.</p>
        <p>
            <h5 class="title is-5">Now introducing: The School of White Trash</h5>
        </p>

        <p>
            Nashville is notorious for being the home of people who aren’t “from” Nashville. Many newcomers hail from distant cities- anonymous, soulless places where one can have trouble establishing an “identity.” Besides job or girlfriend, more than
            a few young men come to the South looking for-wait for it-“authenticity.”
        </p>
        <p>Well, give it to them. Your business will be to establish a school for real southern men aka rednecks(I’m not talking about the seersucker, mint julip tea drinking dandy. Different subject, different time). </p>
        <p>
            As far as the school goes, get a building not too far out-one that is preferably in a dodgy part of town, the dodgier the better actually. If you do it right, your customers will feel brave and manly just for showing up. Here you will teach
            the redneck wannabe how to relax that slack jaw and tighten those rs. You will teach them how to throw knives at a spot in the dirt; make their friends believe stories that could not, would not and will never happen; take apart an engine
            and sort of put it back together so it works for a little while anyway. You will teach them how to make moonshine-the real stuff, not what they sell in Gatlinburg. It’s easy, all you need is water and…just google it. It doesn’t have to
            be perfect or even good. Just make it strong. There is a reason it is illegal.
        </p>
        <p>
            Maybe even take a field trip out to the country and let them shoot broken down refrigerators with shotguns. Oh yeah, to be an effective redneck, one has to know how to fight. You, the instructor, don’t have to know how to fight that well,
            you just need to be able to fight better than your student. This sounds like Fight Club you say. Hmm, my inner entrepreneur who is focused on the goal ahead never heard of it. And btw, you need to stop throwing wrenches in people’s plans.
        </p>
        <p>
            On Saturday nights you host line dancing where the redneck padawans can regale the ladies with the rotgut moonshine they made over the past week. They can impress with the stupid stories they make up during the week, they can line dance, pick
            fights over each other’s dance partners, and get in real authentic bar fights. And on Monday mornings, they can go into cubicles with black-eyed and stitched up heads held high. Thanks to you and your service, they will authentically be…
            something.
        </p>
        <br />
        <p>
            <h5 class="title is-5">Great Football players are built, not recruited.</h5>
        </p>
        <p>
            If that idea doesn’t sound like you then here is another, albeit a little more involved than the last one. If you’ve lived here anytime at all and spent most of it somewhere other than a rock, you should know that football is cherished thing
            in this part of the country. And, especially in the Eastern part of the state, University of Tennessee football is as close to a sacrament as one can get in these Jesus loving parts without being sacrilegious. But over the years UT football
            has had its problems, one being that Vanderbilt has beaten UT three times in the past so many years. I’ll say no more. And while there is plenty of handwringing and coach throwing under the bus, there are precious few solutions other than
            getting another coach who can recruit better players. Getting a new coach is like anything else in life: getting a new job, a house, a spouse, or a new life. In other words, it’s a game of craps, a hand of blackjack, a pick behind door
            number three hoping it’s not the ugly couch the game show producers found in a warehouse in Long Beach.
        </p>
        <p>
            No, UT needs better players without the uncertainty associated with an unknown coach's recruiting skills. And that’s where your business comes in. Trump, like many Americans, believes that we need to bring manufacturing home instead of looking
            to other countries to outsource goods and services to. Likewise, UT- instead of looking for players all over the country needs to look for them here in our backyard. Now sure we have good players, but you can’t just wait for good players
            to be born, grow up, and possibly be contenders. No, we need to start building them.
        </p>
        <p>
            Think about it. Nashville is a major focal point of healthcare. Healthcare involves biology and biotech which is exactly what we need to build the football players we need. Simply put, the UT football world needs a performance enhancement
            drug-not steroids because those are illegal-but something else that’s…not so illegal. Now, this particular endeavor may involve a degree or two, but not your non-existent degree. Someone else’s, someone who has just gotten out of medical
            school or a Ph.D. program somewhere and who is
        </p>
        <br />
        <div style="padding-left:15px">
            <ul style="list-style-type:disc">
                <li>Glad to be out of school </li>
                <li>Probably in serious debt, and therefore</li>
                <li>Desperate enough to be open to any crazy ideas you might.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <br />

        <p>
            Remember, channel your inner Trump. And if you can’t find a Ph.D. here who is bat-brained enough to go along with this business, then go to China and get one there. I know what I said about Trump, but if Ivanka can get her shoes from China
            for reselling here in America, then you can get you’re Ph.D. there as well. Visa in hand, start calling up those UT alumni and boosters and who have money, and nothing to spend it on other than their bratty entitled children. That
            and UT football.
        </p>
        <p>
            Admittedly there is more involved in this side hustle than the prior one. There may be some uncomfortable conversations that involve stem cells and such. Buck up. Again this is UT football-accommodations can and will be made, and you’ll get through it. Another more difficult aspect is that this side hustle is more of a long game than the prior one. It may take a generation to get results; that’s a long span in football program rebuilding time. And UT alumni are notoriously impatient as far as getting wins are concerned. A head coach as at best five years to turn things around. And we’re talking at least eighteen for this side hustle.
        </p>
        <p>
            If you are on your A game, then this can be a nice little side career. For eighteen years you live off the funding while letting your Ph.D. do all the work until the ship comes in. And if that ship doesn’t come in then you live off the funding until the sponsor pulls the cord. And if it does then once again UT will be a national contender. Fans, alumni, anybody who cares about UT Football will salute you.  And you will have your very own one bedroom in the Gulch.
        </p>
    </article>

